# AWS ELASTIC BEANSTALK (EASY STEP-BY-STEP)
## WHAT IS ELASTIC BEANSTALK?
Platform as a Service (PaaS) to deploy web applications without managing servers.
---
## PREREQUISITE
- Your application file ready (.war / .zip / code)
---
## STEP 1: OPEN ELASTIC BEANSTALK
1. Go to AWS Console  
2. Search Elastic Beanstalk  
3. Click Elastic Beanstalk  
4. Click Create application  
---
## STEP 2: CREATE APPLICATION
1. Application name: MyApp  
2. Description: (optional)  
3. Click Create  
---
## STEP 3: CREATE ENVIRONMENT
1. Click Create environment  
2. Select Web server environment  
3. Click Select  
---
## STEP 4: CONFIGURE ENVIRONMENT
1. Environment name: MyApp-env  
2. Choose platform:
   - Tomcat (for .war)  
   - Node.js / Python / PHP (based on your app)  
3. Under Application code:
   - Select Upload your code  
   - Upload your .war or .zip file  
---
## STEP 5: CONFIGURE SERVICE ACCESS
1. Service role: Select existing (LabRole)  
2. EC2 Key pair: Optional  
3. EC2 Instance profile: LabInstanceProfile  
---
## STEP 6: CONFIGURE NETWORK
1. VPC: Default  
2. Subnets: Default  
3. Enable Public IP  
---
## STEP 7: INSTANCE & SCALING
1. Instance type: t2.micro  
2. Min instances: 1  
3. Max instances: 2  
4. Load balancer: Enabled (recommended)  
---
## STEP 8: REVIEW & CREATE
1. Click Review  
2. Click Create  
---
## DEPLOYMENT (AUTOMATIC)
AWS will create:
- EC2 instance  
- Load balancer  
- Auto Scaling group  
- Security groups  
---
## ACCESS YOUR APPLICATION
1. After deployment completes  
2. Copy the provided URL  
3. Open in browser  
Your application will run 🎉  
---
## UPDATE APPLICATION
1. Go to your environment  
2. Click Upload and Deploy  
3. Upload new version  
---
## RESULT
- App deployed without managing servers  
- Auto scaling + load balancing handled automatically  
---
## ONE-LINE UNDERSTANDING
Upload code → Beanstalk handles everything → App runs on cloud
